title: Excitation functions of natNe(3He,x)22,24Na and natNe(a,x)22,24Na processes: investigation of production of 22Na and 24Na at a medium-sized cyclotron

x4freetext: Targets were natural neon gas. Pressure was 1 bar for
deuteron irradiation and 3 bar for p, 3He and alpha
used max 3 cells were placed in one stack. Cell window
was made of Al, Ti or Ag. Beam current was determined
by Faraday-cup and by using monitor reactions.
The max. difference between the two method was about
30%. The difference in the beam current determined by
by two monitor reactions was about 5%.
For deuteron irradiation the cells were irradiated
Decay data were taken from E.Browne, R.Firestone, Table
The uncertainty was determined by using the
primary uncertainty, the straggling effect, stopping
uncertainty and it ranges from 0.5 to 3.2 MeV.
The cross section error was obtained by summing in
quadrature the relative errors of the factors encounted
Taking an aliquot of rinse solution (10%)
Membrane effect of the target windows (3%)
The total error of cross section are about 17%
